# Commit Message Guidelines

## Format

- Always use the conventional commit format
- Always suggest a conventional commit with a type and optional scope in
  lowercase letters

## Structure

```text
type(scope): description

body (optional)

footer (optional)
```

## Types

- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `style`: Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
- `refactor`: Code refactoring
- `test`: Adding or updating tests
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks

## Examples

- `feat(templates): add preferred tools management`
- `fix(server): resolve database path issue`
- `docs: update architecture documentation`

## Requirements

- Keep the commit message concise and within 60 characters for the subject line
- Ensure the commit message is ready to be pasted into the terminal without
  further editing
- Use lowercase for type and scope
